  <diagram id="concept-comparison" name="SCOM vs Azure Monitor">
    <!--
      STUB — SCOM ↔ Azure Monitor Concept Comparison
      ================================================
      Design intent (from PLAN.md):
        Dual-column layout.
        Left column:  SCOM concepts
        Right column: Azure Monitor equivalents
        Dashed connecting lines between matched concepts.

      SCOM (left)                        Azure Monitor (right)
      ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      Management Pack                 ←→  DCR + Alert Rules + Workbook
      Distributed Application         ←→  Service Group + Root Entity
      Health Model (rollup tree)      ←→  Azure Monitor Health Model (preview)
      Unit Monitor                    ←→  Signal on an Entity
      Aggregate Monitor               ←→  Generic Entity (aggregating children)
      Dependency Monitor              ←→  Relationship with health propagation
      Green / Yellow / Red            ←→  Healthy / Degraded / Unhealthy
      Discovery                       ←→  Azure Resource Graph auto-discovery
      Override                        ←→  Signal threshold / Impact setting
      Notification Subscription       ←→  Action Group
      Data Warehouse                  ←→  Log Analytics Workspace
      Operations Console              ←→  Azure Portal + Workbooks + Grafana

      See docs/comparison/index.md for the rendered table version.
      Open this file in draw.io (app.diagrams.net) to build the full diagram.
    -->
